You can achieve this by using Google Apps Script in Google Sheets. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it:

1. Open your Google Sheet with the "capture" and "preparar" sheets.

2. Click on "Extensions" in the menu bar, then select "Apps Script".

3. In the Apps Script editor, delete any code that is already there and paste the following code:

```javascript
function onEdit(e) {
  var range = e.range;
  var sheet = range.getSheet();

  if (sheet.getName() == "capture" && range.getColumn() == 7 && e.value == "pass to sheet 2") {
    var rowValues = range.offset(0, -6, 1, 6).getValues()[0];
    var prepararSheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("preparar");

    prepararSheet.appendRow(rowValues);
    sheet.deleteRow(range.getRow());
  }
}
```

4. Click on the disk icon to save the script and give it a name.

5. Close the Apps Script editor and go back to your Google Sheet.

Now, whenever you select "pass to sheet 2" in the dropdown menu in the 7th column of the "capture" sheet, the data from that row will be copied to the "preparar" sheet and the row will be deleted from the "capture" sheet.
